From 3d6330683f9b5030bb66640fde2e5f890f1c268f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alexander Hoffman <alxhoff@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 23 Mar 2026 14:52:23 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 15/32] d4xx: Refactor HWMC interface with improved error
 handling and named constants

Comprehensive cleanup of the Hardware Monitor Command (HWMC) interface:
- Add verbose error reporting to ds5_get_hwmc with specific error codes
- Migrate GVD (Get Version Data) to use the common ds5_X_hwmc functions
- Fix GVD buffer length from 239 to 276 bytes to match firmware spec
- Add validation for invalid V4L2 control IDs
- Improve ds5_X_with_check error verbosity with function and register
  context
- Replace hardcoded hex HWMC register addresses with named constants
- Add bounds checking for HWMC_RW buffer sizes
---
 kernel/nvidia/drivers/media/i2c/d4xx.c | 183 +++++++++++++++++--------
 1 file changed, 123 insertions(+), 60 deletions(-)

diff --git a/kernel/nvidia/drivers/media/i2c/d4xx.c b/kernel/nvidia/drivers/media/i2c/d4xx.c
index 2def19a25..4ccec3ef8 100644
